            <p>Based on our live catalog, the average price per can is <strong>€{avgPricePerCan.toFixed(2)}</strong>, with a range of €{minPricePerCan.toFixed(2)}–€{maxPricePerCan.toFixed(2)}. The average price per individual pouch is <strong>€{avgPricePerPouch.toFixed(2)}</strong>.</p>
            <p>Budget brands average €{avgBudgetPrice.toFixed(2)} per can. Mid-range brands average €{avgMidPrice.toFixed(2)}. Premium brands average €{avgPremiumPrice.toFixed(2)}.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details style="margin: 24px 0; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; rounded-xl; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 12px;">
        <summary style="padding: 16px; background: #f9fafb; cursor: pointer; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-weight: 600;">
            How does nicotine pouch cost compare to cigarettes and vaping?
            <span style="color: #6b7280;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div style="padding: 16px; border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">
            <p><strong>Cigarettes</strong> cost €8–€12 per 20-pack, or €32–€48 monthly. <strong>Vaping liquid</strong> averages €15–€30 per month. <strong>Nicotine pouches</strong> cost €{lightMonthlyCost.toFixed(0)}–€{heavyMonthlyCost.toFixed(0)} per month depending on usage.</p>
            <p>For moderate users, pouches fall between vaping and cigarettes in cost. For light users, pouches are cheaper than all alternatives except vaping.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details style="margin: 24px 0; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; rounded-xl; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 12px;">
        <summary style="padding: 16px; background: #f9fafb; cursor: pointer; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-weight: 600;">
            Do larger pack sizes offer a discount?
            <span style="color: #6b7280;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div style="padding: 16px; border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">
            <p>Yes. Single cans are sold at full retail price. Packs of 3+ offer 5–20% savings per can. A 10-pack typically costs 15% less per can than a single. A 30-pack can drop to 20–25% less per can.</p>
            <p>Always compare the total cost, not the package price. A €30 10-pack is a better deal than a €3.50 single can.</p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <h2>Final Thoughts: Budget Your Pouch Use</h2>

    <p>Nicotine pouches aren't the cheapest nicotine option — that title goes to vaping liquid. But they're far cheaper than cigarettes and competitive with nicotine gum. For a moderate user, expect to spend €{moderateMonthlyCost.toFixed(0)}–€{(moderateMonthlyCost * 1.5).toFixed(0)} per month.</p>
    <p>The key to saving? Buy bulk, stick to budget or mid-range brands, and rotate strengths to extend your supply. Over a year, choosing a budget 10-pack over premium singles can save €100+.</p>

    <div style="background: #f0fdf4; border-left: 4px solid #22c55e; padding: 24px; margin: 32px 0; border-radius: 6px;">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Explore Related Guides</h3>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
            <li><a href="/blog/best-budget-nicotine-pouches">Find the cheapest quality pouches</a></li>
            <li><a href="/nicotine-pouch-brands-compared">Compare all brands side-by-side</a></li>
            <li><a href="/blog/nicotine-pouch-subscription-guide">Learn about recurring discount programs</a></li>
            <li><a href="/products">Browse all pouches by price</a></li>
